cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the performance analysis and synthesis of distributed system throttlers. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses network bandwidth usage and communication link modifications. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with controlling the flow rate of incoming metrics to protect a service's backend/clients from getting overloaded. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as throttling can be used as a security measure to prevent denial-of-service attacks. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also a possible category as the paper studies the performance deterioration of DSTs subject to demand uncertainty and aims to improve their performance via optimal design.
